claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus comprising:
a first switching circuit configured to receive a differential data signal and a first bias voltage, wherein the first switching circuit is configured to convert the differential data signal to a first PMOS drive signal and a second PMOS drive signal for a first PMOS driver transistor and a second PMOS driver transistor, respectively, wherein the first switching circuit is configured to change a state of the first and second PMOS drive signals in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding PMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the first bias voltage, wherein a second state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding PMOS driver transistor;
a second switching circuit configured to receive the differential data signal and a second bias voltage, wherein the second switching circuit is configured to convert the differential data signal to a first NMOS drive signal and a second NMOS drive signal for a first NMOS driver transistor and a second NMOS driver transistor, wherein the second switching circuit is configured to change a state of the NMOS drive signal in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding NMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the second bias voltage, and wherein a second state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding NMOS driver transistor;
a first multiplexer configured to select at least between a first signal input and a second signal input different from the first signal input by phase and/or delay to generate the differential data signal for the first switching circuit and the second switching circuit;
a third switching circuit configured to receive a second differential data signal and configured to convert the second differential data signal to third and fourth PMOS drive signals for third and fourth PMOS driver transistors, respectively;
a fourth switching circuit configured to receive the second differential data signal and configured to convert the second differential data signal to third and fourth NMOS drive signals for third and fourth NMOS driver transistors, respectively; and
a second multiplexer configured to select at least between a first signal input and a second signal input different from the first signal input by phase and/or delay to generate the second differential data signal, wherein the first multiplexer and the second multiplexer select the same signal for normal operation and select different signals for a squelch mode.

2. The apparatus of claim 1:
wherein the first switching circuit further comprises:
a first NMOS transistor;
a second NMOS transistor, wherein sources of the first NMOS transistor and the second NMOS transistor are electrically connected to a first node;
a first capacitor;
a second capacitor; and
a first enable switch configured to receive the first bias voltage and to selectively provide the first bias voltage to the first node,
wherein the first switching circuit is configured to generate the first state of the first and second PMOS drive signals via capacitive coupling and to generate the second state of the first and second PMOS drive signals via a combination of capacitive coupling and turning on of at least one of the first NMOS transistor or the second NMOS transistor; and

wherein the second switching circuit further comprises:
a first PMOS transistor;
a second PMOS transistor, wherein sources of the first PMOS transistor and the second PMOS transistor are electrically connected to a second node;
a third capacitor;
a fourth capacitor;
a second enable switch configured to receive the second bias voltage and to selectively provide the second bias voltage to the second node;
wherein the second switching circuit is configured to generate the first state of the first and second NMOS drive signals via capacitive coupling and to generate the second state of the first and second NMOS drive signals via a combination of capacitive coupling and turning on of at least one of the first PMOS transistor or the second NMOS transistor.

5. The apparatus of claim 2:
wherein the first capacitor has a first end and a second end, wherein the first end is configured to receive a first signal of the differential data signal, wherein the second end is electrically connected to a third node comprising a gate of the first NMOS transistor and a drain of the second NMOS transistor, wherein the third node is configured to provide the first PMOS drive signal;
wherein the second capacitor has a first end and a second end, wherein the first end is configured to receive a second signal of the differential data signal, wherein the second end is electrically connected to a fourth node comprising a gate of the second NMOS transistor and a drain of the first NMOS transistor, wherein the fourth node is configured to provide the second PMOS drive signal;
wherein the third capacitor has a first end and a second end, wherein the first end is configured to receive the first signal of the differential data signal, wherein the second end is electrically connected to a fifth node comprising a gate of the first PMOS transistor and a drain of the second PMOS transistor, wherein the fifth node is configured to provide the first NMOS drive signal; and
wherein the fourth capacitor has a first end and a second end, wherein the first end is configured to receive the second signal of the differential data signal, wherein the second end is electrically connected to a sixth node comprising a gate of the second PMOS transistor and a drain of the first PMOS transistor, wherein the sixth node is configured to provide the second NMOS drive signal.

6. An apparatus comprising:
a first switching circuit configured to receive a differential data signal and a first bias voltage, wherein the first switching circuit is configured to convert the differential data signal to a first PMOS drive signal and a second PMOS drive signal for a first PMOS driver transistor and a second PMOS driver transistor, respectively, wherein the first switching circuit is configured to change a state of the first and second PMOS drive signals in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding PMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the first bias voltage, wherein a second state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding PMOS driver transistor;
a second switching circuit configured to receive the differential data signal and a second bias voltage, wherein the second switching circuit is configured to convert the differential data signal to a first NMOS drive signal and a second NMOS drive signal for a first NMOS driver transistor and a second NMOS driver transistor, wherein the second switching circuit is configured to change a state of the NMOS drive signal in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding NMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the second bias voltage, and wherein a second state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding NMOS driver transistor;
a third switching circuit configured to receive a second differential data signal and to receive the first bias voltage, the third switching circuit further configured to convert the second differential data signal to third and fourth PMOS drive signals for third and fourth PMOS driver transistors, respectively;
a fourth switching circuit configured to receive the second differential data signal and to receive the first bias voltage, the fourth switching circuit further configured to convert the second differential data signal to third and fourth NMOS drive signals for third and fourth NMOS driver transistors, respectively;
a first switch configured to receive the first bias voltage and a first control signal, wherein the first switch is configured to selectively provide the first bias voltage to at least one of the first switching circuit or the third switching circuit;
a second switch configured to receive the second bias voltage and a second control signal, wherein the second switch is configured to selectively provide the second bias voltage to at least one of the second switching circuit or the fourth switching circuit;
a first DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the first switching circuit;
a second DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the second switching circuit;
a third DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the third switching circuit; and
a fourth DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the fourth switching circuit;
wherein for normal operation:
the first switch and the second switch are controlled to provide the first bias voltage and the second bias voltage, respectively; and
the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are disabled;

wherein for squelched operation:
the first switch and the second switch are controlled to turn off; and
the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are enabled and the inputs to the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are provided such that the PMOS driver transistors are in contention with the NMOS driver transistors.

7. The apparatus of claim 6, further comprising:
a first voltage regulator configured to generate a first regulated voltage based on the first bias voltage, a coupling efficiency associated with the first switching circuit or the second switching circuit, and a first power supply voltage rail, wherein the received data signal is provided by circuits powered by the first power supply voltage rail, and wherein the PMOS driver transistor and the NMOS driver transistor are powered by a second power supply voltage rail higher than the first power supply voltage rail; and
a second voltage regulator configured to generate a second regulated voltage based on the second bias voltage, the coupling efficiency, and the first power supply voltage rail;
wherein output transistors of the first and third DC-coupled switching circuits are powered by the first regulated voltage;
wherein output transistors of the second and fourth DC-coupled switching circuits are powered by the second regulated voltage.

8. The apparatus of claim 7:
wherein the first regulated voltage is substantially equal to the first bias voltage summed with a product of the coupling efficiency and the first power supply voltage rail;
wherein the second regulated voltage is substantially equal to a difference between the second bias voltage and the product of the coupling efficiency and the first power supply voltage rail.

9. A method for driving a transistor, the method comprising:
receiving a differential data signal and a first bias voltage in a first switching circuit;
converting, using the first switching circuit, the differential data signal to a first PMOS drive signal and a second PMOS drive signal for a first PMOS driver transistor and a second PMOS driver transistor, respectively;
changing, using the first switching circuit, a state of the first and second PMOS drive signals in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding PMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the first bias voltage, wherein a second state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding PMOS driver transistor;
receiving the differential data signal and a second bias voltage in a second switching circuit;
converting, using the second switching circuit, the differential data signal to a first NMOS drive signal and a second NMOS drive signal for a first NMOS driver transistor and a second NMOS driver transistor;
changing, using the second switching circuit, a state of the NMOS drive signal in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding NMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the second bias voltage, and wherein a second state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding NMOS driver transistor;
selecting at least between a first signal input and a second signal input different from the first signal input by phase and/or delay to generate the differential data signal for the first switching circuit and the second switching circuit;
receiving a second differential data signal in a third switching circuit;
converting, using the third switching circuit, the second differential data signal to third and fourth PMOS drive signals for third and fourth PMOS driver transistors, respectively;
receiving the second differential data signal in a fourth switching circuit;
converting, using the fourth switching circuit, the second differential data signal to third and fourth NMOS drive signals for third and fourth NMOS driver transistors, respectively; and
selecting at least between a first signal input and a second signal input different from the first signal input by phase and/or delay to generate the second differential data signal, wherein the same signal is selected for normal operation and different signals are selected for a squelch mode.

10. A method for driving a transistor, the method comprising:
receiving a differential data signal and a first bias voltage in a first switching circuit;
converting, using the first switching circuit, the differential data signal to a first PMOS drive signal and a second PMOS drive signal for a first PMOS driver transistor and a second PMOS driver transistor, respectively;
changing, using the first switching circuit, a state of the first and second PMOS drive signals in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding PMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the first bias voltage, wherein a second state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding PMOS driver transistor;
receiving the differential data signal and a second bias voltage in a second switching circuit;
converting, using the second switching circuit, the differential data signal to a first NMOS drive signal and a second NMOS drive signal for a first NMOS driver transistor and a second NMOS driver transistor;
changing, using the second switching circuit, a state of the NMOS drive signal in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding NMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the second bias voltage, and wherein a second state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding NMOS driver transistor;
receiving a second differential data signal and the first bias voltage in a third switching circuit;
converting, using the third switching circuit, the second differential data signal to third and fourth PMOS drive signals for third and fourth PMOS driver transistors, respectively;
receiving the second differential data signal and the first bias voltage in a fourth switching circuit;
converting, using the fourth switching circuit, the second differential data signal to third and fourth NMOS drive signals for third and fourth NMOS driver transistors, respectively;
receiving the first bias voltage and a first control signal in a first switch;
selectively providing, using the first switch, the first bias voltage to at least one of the first switching circuit or the third switching circuit;
receiving the second bias voltage and a second control signal in a second switch;
selectively providing, using the second switch, the second bias voltage to at least one of the second switching circuit or the fourth switching circuit;
providing a first DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the first switching circuit;
providing a second DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the second switching circuit;
providing a third DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the third switching circuit; and
providing a fourth DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the fourth switching circuit;
wherein for normal operation:
the first switch and the second switch are controlled to provide the first bias voltage and the second bias voltage, respectively; and
the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are disabled;

wherein for squelched operation:
the first switch and the second switch are controlled to turn off; and
the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are enabled and the inputs to the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are provided such that the PMOS driver transistors are in contention with the NMOS driver transistors.

11. The method of claim 10, further comprising:
wherein the first switching circuit comprises a first capacitor, a second capacitor, a first NMOS transistor, a second NMOS transistor, and the first switch, wherein sources of the first NMOS transistor and the second NMOS transistor are electrically connected to a first node;
selectively providing the first bias voltage to the first node;
wherein changing further comprises:
generating the first state of the first and second PMOS drive signals via capacitive coupling, wherein a first state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding PMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the first bias voltage,
generating the second state of the first and second PMOS drive signals via a combination of capacitive coupling and turning on of at least one of the first NMOS transistor or the second NMOS transistor, wherein a second state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding PMOS driver transistor;

wherein the second switching circuit comprises a third capacitor, a fourth capacitor, a first PMOS transistor, a second PMOS transistor, and the second switch, wherein sources of the first PMOS transistor and the second PMOS transistor are electrically connected to a second node;
selectively providing the second bias voltage to the second node;
wherein changing further comprises:
generating the first state of the first and second NMOS drive signals via capacitive coupling, wherein a first state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding NMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the second bias voltage, and
generating the second state of the first and second NMOS drive signals via a combination of capacitive coupling and turning on of at least one of the first PMOS transistor or the second NMOS transistor, wherein a second state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding NMOS driver transistor.

15. The method of claim 10, further comprising:
generating, using a first voltage regulator, a first regulated voltage based on the first bias voltage, a coupling efficiency associated with the first switching circuit or the second switching circuit, and a first power supply voltage rail, wherein the received data signal is provided by circuits powered by the first power supply voltage rail, and wherein the PMOS driver transistor and the NMOS driver transistor are powered by a second power supply voltage rail higher than the first power supply voltage rail;
generating, using a second voltage regulator, a second regulated voltage based on the second bias voltage, the coupling efficiency, and the first power supply voltage rail;
powering output transistors of the first and third DC-coupled switching circuits with the first regulated voltage; and
powering output transistors of the second and fourth DC-coupled switching circuits with the second regulated voltage.

16. The method of claim 15:
wherein the first regulated voltage is substantially equal to the first bias voltage summed with a product of the coupling efficiency and the first power supply voltage rail;
wherein the second regulated voltage is substantially equal to a difference between the second bias voltage and the product of the coupling efficiency and the first power supply voltage rail.

17. An apparatus for driving a transistor, the apparatus comprising:
a first means for receiving a differential data signal and a first bias voltage, wherein the first receiving means includes capacitively coupled paths and switched paths;
a means for converting the differential data signal to a first PMOS drive signal and a second PMOS drive signal for a first PMOS driver transistor and a second PMOS driver transistor, respectively;
a means for changing a state of the first and second PMOS drive signals in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding PMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the first bias voltage, wherein a second state of the first or second PMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding PMOS driver transistor;
a second means for receiving the differential data signal and a second bias voltage, wherein the second receiving means includes capacitively coupled paths and switched paths;
a means for converting the differential data signal to a first NMOS drive signal and a second NMOS drive signal for a first NMOS driver transistor and a second NMOS driver transistor;
a means for changing a state of the NMOS drive signal in response to a change in state of the data signal, wherein a first state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns on the corresponding NMOS driver transistor and has a voltage level of the second bias voltage, and wherein a second state of the first or second NMOS drive signal turns off the corresponding NMOS driver transistor; and
a third means for receiving a second differential data signal and the first bias voltage, wherein the third receiving means is configured to convert the second differential data signal to third and fourth PMOS drive signals for third and fourth PMOS driver transistors, respectively;
a fourth means for receiving the second differential data signal and the first bias voltage, wherein the fourth receiving means is configure to convert the second differential data signal to third and fourth NMOS drive signals for third and fourth NMOS driver transistors, respectively;
a first switch configured to receive the first bias voltage and a first control signal in a first switch, wherein the first switch is further configured to provide the first bias voltage to at least one of the first switching circuit or the third switching circuit;
a second switch configured to receive the second bias voltage and a second control signal, wherein the second switch is further configured to provide the second bias voltage to at least one of the second switching circuit or the fourth switching circuit;
a first DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the first switching circuit;
a second DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the second switching circuit;
a third DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the third switching circuit; and
a fourth DC-coupled switching circuit in parallel with the fourth switching circuit;
wherein for normal operation:
the first switch and the second switch are controlled to provide the first bias voltage and the second bias voltage, respectively; and
the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are disabled;

wherein for squelched operation:
the first switch and the second switch are controlled to turn off; and
the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are enabled and the inputs to the first, second, third, and fourth DC paths are provided such that the PMOS driver transistors are in contention with the NMOS driver transistors.
